tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE measurement_results (
  measurement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  measurement_value FLOAT,
  measurement_unit VARCHAR(50),
  FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiment_results(experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_experiment_results (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
    experiment_date DATE,
    measurement_1 FLOAT,
    measurement_2 FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_experiment_details (
    detail_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    temperature FLOAT,
    pressure FLOAT,
    time_taken INT
);

CREATE TABLE measurements (
    measurement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    measurement_value FLOAT,
    measurement_unit VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    scientist_id INT,
    result_description TEXT,
    result_analysis_data JSON,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (scientist_id) REFERENCES scientists(scientist_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_notes (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    result_id INT REFERENCES experiment_results(id),
    note_text TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    author_name VARCHAR(255)
);
